    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.01872.005_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">New Britain</name>
                    <date when="1875-04-25">April 25 1875</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Father &amp; Friend</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Your letter came to hand the first of this week and I was glad to hear from you but
                very sorry to hear of your loss of health &amp; bereavement<ptr target="loc.01969_n4"/> this <choice>
                    <sic>liaves</sic>
                    <corr>leaves</corr>
                </choice> me and family all well my little Boy<ptr target="n5001c"/> is growing very fast and is getting
                as fat as he can be <choice>
                    <sic>Worke</sic>
                    <corr>Work</corr>
                </choice> is very <choice>
                    <sic>dul</sic>
                    <corr>dull</corr>
                </choice> here I have only about two days work in a week and 
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.01872.006_large.jpg" type="verso"/> 
                the wages are small I do not <choice>
                    <sic>everage</sic>
                    <corr>average</corr>
                </choice> two dollars a day when I work I am working on locks I do not like the
                place here and shall get away from here as soon as I can How <choice>
                    <sic>Is</sic>
                    <corr>I</corr>
                </choice> work there I can work at most any thing that comes along I should like
                very much to see you and if every thing goes well I may come on to see you this
                summer I got a little behind through the winter and have not quite caught up yet I
                have got a little <choice>
                    <sic>Buisness</sic>
                    <corr>Business</corr>
                </choice> out side of my work which I do Evenings 
                <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.01872.007_large.jpg" type="recto"/> 
                I am connected with <choice>
                    <sic>Sovererns</sic>
                    <corr>Sovereigns</corr>
                </choice> of Industry I Sell Butter &amp; <choice>
                    <sic>Sigars</sic>
                    <corr>Cigars</corr>
                </choice> and that helps me a great deal so that I <choice>
                    <sic>manadge</sic>
                    <corr>manage</corr>
                </choice> to get along And I think by the first of June I shall be all square here
                We deal with a firm in <choice>
                    <sic>Philadefia</sic>
                    <corr>Philadelphia</corr>
                </choice> Clother Bennett &amp; Co Tower Hall I think it is in Market St there is a
                Mr Walters<ptr target="n5001"/> with them and he is coming <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low"
                    resp="#js">on</unclear> here soon to take Orders and <choice>
                    <sic>Measament</sic>
                    <corr>Measurement</corr>
                </choice> for the <choice>
                    <sic>Soverns</sic>
                    <corr>Sovereigns</corr>
                </choice> Do you remember meeting a <choice>
                    <sic>yong</sic>
                    <corr>young</corr>
                </choice> Lady with me at the corner of Fulton and Court Sts once that is my wife
                she remembers you well so good <choice>
                    <sic>by</sic>
                    <corr>bye</corr>
                </choice>
                <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc.01872.008_large.jpg" type="verso"/> for this time I
                will try to write oftener in future we all send love</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>from your <choice>
                        <sic>affecinat</sic>
                        <corr>affectionate</corr>
                    </choice> son &amp;c</salute>
                <signed>J. M. Rogers.</signed>
            </closer>
            <note type="editorial" place="bottom" resp="#ww">John M. Rogers New Britain Conn April
                26. '75</note>
